---
title: One-Pan Tuscan Tomato & White Beans with Zucchini, Ricotta & Parmesan Croutons
description: Love the flavors of pizza? Of course, you do, you’re only human! That’s why our chefs channeled our favorite late-night bite into a one-pan dinner that’s packed with veggies and protein. Zucchini and cannellini beans simmer with tomatoes for the saucy component. That’s dolloped with creamy, mild ricotta cheese. Then say hello to big and crunchy croutons. They cover the top with some Parmesan, which becomes all melty when popped into the oven. Where has this skillet bean all our lives??
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62f2abfe7647921db2032ed9-6ad54449.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-tuscan-tomato-white-beans-62f2abfe7647921db2032ed9-9854799b.pdf
course: main course
time required: 30m
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 16 g
  sodium: 2250 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-tuscan-tomato-white-beans-62f2abfe7647921db2032ed9
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice into quarter-moons. Dice @tomato{2} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat.

Add onion, @salt{1/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly browned, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of oil, zucchini, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is softened, ~{4-7%minutes}.

Add @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the @chili powder{1%tsp}, half the fresh tomatoes, and @diced tomatoes{1/3%cup}. Cook, stirring, until mixture has slightly thickened, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> Save the rest of the diced tomatoes for another use.

While veggies cook, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise. Brush cut sides with a large drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Toast, cut sides up, directly on oven rack until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Transfer toasted baguette to a #cutting board{}. Dice into 1-inch croutons.

Add @cannellini beans{1%can} and their liquid, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1/4%cup} to pan with veggies. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Remove from heat. Stir in remaining fresh tomatoes.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer filling to a small #baking dish{} now.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and pepper.

Dollop ricotta over skillet. Top with croutons and @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}.

Bake on top rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Garnish skillet with chopped parsley. Divide between plates or serve directly from pan.